Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Transfer half to a small #bowl{} and roughly mash them using a #potato masher{} or the back of a #fork{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the onion and @diced chorizo{90%g} to the pan and stir-fry until the chorizo is starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @smoked paprika{1%sachet}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, black beans (both mashed and whole), @vegetable stock paste{15%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} for the soup to the pan.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil. Lower the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Cheesy Mini Toasts ==

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Halve the @ciabatta{1}, then cut into 1cm slices. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Pop the ciabatta slices onto a medium #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the cheese and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Grill on the top shelf until melted and golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

== Finishing the Soup ==

While the ciabatta grills, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%g}, corn, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @butter{20%g} through the soup until combined. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @?water{1%splash} if it's a little thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the soup between your #bowls{}.

Serve the cheesy toasts alongside for dipping and scooping.

Enjoy!

> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Chipotle Chorizo, Corn and Black Bean Soup in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.